urgence of interest among students and educators of calculus today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCalculus. 0aProcesses, Infinite. 7aMATHEMATICS / General.2bisacsh  ateaching, instruction, classroom, teacher, academic, math, mathematics, stem, history, historical, scholarly, research, pedagogy, professor, student, facts, techniques, problem solving, memorization, ideas, intellectual, greek, ancient world, archimedes, pythagoras, euclid, kepler, galileo, fermat, newton, leibniz, educator, college, university, higher ed, textbook.1 aBressoud, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831106353860 cprintz978022680668640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226806693423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226806693/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles